href="jms-001S.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-001S">pointed</fr:link> dcpo <fr:tex>A</fr:tex>.</fr:p>

  <fr:p>We define the structure map <fr:tex>\alpha</fr:tex> to take <fr:tex>u \in \mathsf { L } {A}</fr:tex> to the <fr:link
href="jms-001U.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-001U">supremum of the semidirected subset</fr:link> <fr:tex>{ \mathopen {} \left \{ x \in  A  \mid  u =  \eta _Ax \right \} \mathclose {}}</fr:tex>, so we may write <fr:tex>\alpha  u =  \bigsqcup _{p:u{ \downarrow }}u[p]</fr:tex>. It is not difficult to see that this assignment is continuous.</fr:p>

